📣 Fun fact: I own/admin/mod not 1 but 8 Facebook Groups!

1. You Know You're A Poler When... 
A silly pole group that started over a decade ago.  It has over 30K members now and is still an active community!
2. You Know You're A Pole Instructor When 
Branching off of YKYAPW - a collection of pole instructors for resources and information. 
3. You Know You're A Business Poler When 
Last in the Collection - a buying / selling / marketing group for the pole community. 
4. The Pole Academy - Greenville, SC 
@thepoleacademy 
My studio's group for students and the Greenville pole community 
5. Dayseeker Fans 
@dayseeker
A band I truly love and want to see grow. I hope they receive all the recognition they deserve. Love the band? Join 'Dayseeker Fans' - the Officially Unofficial FB Group!
6. The Fang Gang- Conditioning, Floorwork & Stretch with Hoodlum Fang 
@hoodlumfang's online community where Instructors including myself share tips, training and more!
7. NC & SC Pole Dancers & Aerialists 
NC & SC pole community page to share events and shenanigans 
8. POLERINOS 
@myfavoritemurder
Where true crime meets pole dance. A space for us murderinos / true crime fans to cross over our love of pole dance & Fitness!

Join Jax & Ally in this guided partner stretching workshop accessible to all levels!

@poler_eclipse @jaxpole @thepoleacademy

They will show you an essential warm up, how to communicate with a partner and proper, effective stretches to help increase flexibility, range of motion and body awareness.

This workshop will focus of different areas of shoulder work, back bends and hip openers.

The event is Saturday, June 10th @ 10A. It will last 90 minutes and is $25/person. You're welcome to bring a partner or pair up with a buddy in the class. Yoga mats, resistance bands and blocks are provided at the studio but feel free to bring your own. Wear comfortable, layered clothing to stay warm and allow to you to be mobile.

Sign Up @ www.thepoleacademy.com and purchase a Workshop credit for the class.

Jax became a Hoodlum Fang Ambassador in early 2019 and has enjoyed being a part of such a unique partnership!

Hoodlum Fang caught her eye solely because of the prints that were available. After seeing so many options in the pole community - none quite attracted her dark side until the variety that HF had to offer! Not only were the prints fabulous and came in a range of styles for tops, bottoms and so much more but they fit well too!

Jax was never petite and after trying on so many pole sets from other retailers, well - you can imagine how frustrating it is to find a good fit! Not only did the sizes fit well, they were easy to breathe and move in but also could create custom sizes AND prints! Mind. Blown. Chlo and HF embraced Jax's alternative style, curvy figure and overall eccentric personality - a match made in heaven!

Over the past year HF has grown not just in providing new accessories or styles but in their core values. They acknowledge diversity and support all body figures, genders, skin colors and so much more. Jax has always had an open door policy not only at her studio but in her heart and it was exciting to see her budding partnership also hold those same values. HF is welcoming to their growing Ambassadors and their retail clients. Jax is thrilled to be a part of something that goes so much further than just comfy, cute pole clothes (even though she wants every print!) and has a relationship with a company that isn't afraid to take a stand, use their voice and will back up their team. Hoodlum Fang is so much more than just a clothing store - it's a part of the community and Jax is so happy to be in their family!

💜 Family is love. 💜

I hate -most- people. Don't we all? That's what we have in common. We think we'd NEVER be in a group or have so many schedules to juggle for coffee and dinners.  That we're better off alone. 

We're not. We need people. Although we hate to admit it (Cancer season,  am I right?) we need people. I need people. But not just any ol person. MY people. MY weirdos, goofballs,  silly and kind needs who love pole and concerts and coffee and music to break the silence, saving text messages and letters to re-read them, singing in the car while people stare,  comfortable silences, and - and trustworthy, selfless folks. - Those - are my people. 

I love my adopted family of students, teachers,  friends and the very few blood lines I have left.  You all make my world complete.  You love. You respect. You listen. You care. 

Tell the people you love that you love them everyday. How else will they know? 
Don't be stingy with your words.  Openly care and be open to its return. 

Love your family - however you create it.

Chair - Climb - Dolphin

🎂 BIRTHDAY SHENANIGANS 🎂

I have the best friends (not to brag but definitely going to.) I've never felt so loved and seen than this week and this birthday.  I love my birthday (I'm that annoying person) and I Always plan a get together/ trip/ party, etc. Not this year.  I had all my power of planning taken away (which is new and very rare) in the best way possible. 

I wanted to spend some time on Asheville before a concert on Thursday.  My besties planned a whole day surrounding my favorite things. They surprised me with friends at brunch, an entire hotel decor compete 28th projection sideshow, cupcakes,  charcuterie and sash. We make hotel cocktails before bar hopping, enjoying a tapas dinner with more friends and seeing my favorite bucket list sights I hadn't gotten to explore yet. There were drinks on fire,  puppies in bars, sneaky Speakeasy cocktails and so much more. 

They were so sweet and thoughtful.  I teared up a little during the sideshow and gifts but all that Urban Decay setting spray wouldn't allow more lol

The next day there was coffee in the cutest Cafe, a cat cafe, Witchy stores and of course ended with a concert.  No pit for once but we had the BEST view and most memorable show together. 

All I wanted was to be with those I love and for that it was the best Birthday ever. 

Thank you Shelly  and Joy  for planning everything.  You're both incredible.  Thank you Jarrod  for being in cahoots with my besties and gaslighting me in the best ways to keep everything a surprise.  Thank you Ally for scream singing with us at the concert.  Thank you Bethany for Driving up and spending the evening with me! Thank you to those who joined for meals and drinks - you're so sweet to join me.  Y'all made 37 so memorable 💜

Blue Ridge Rock Festival aka Shit Show Apocalypse 

I survived.  Not from glorious amounts of head banging and throwing crowd surfers like planned but I survived questionable living conditions, fearing for my safety,  an apocalyptic hail storm, riots, flooding and fire. This is not how I wanted to spend my much needed vacation. 

 If you don't know the festival that attended this past weekend is set in Alton, Virginia and it's 4 days of outdoor rock concerts which I look forward to every year and this was my second time attending this event. 

 Last year had its questionable moments but overall was so great that my friends and I decided to go again this year and had something to look forward to.  We felt like we learned a lot last year with RRV camper and all of the potential problems that could arise so we took a plan of action and prepared to the best of our ability learning from arm mistakes and what worked but nothing could prepare us for what actually happened. 

 The first red flag  Was when we pulled into the fairground parking lot at 4:30P on Wednesda  for will call and sat there for hours watching traffic and cars cut in front of us while the lone security officer tried his best to corral thousands of people in the middle of the afternoon on a hot day with no food or water. We have him a Gatorade. 

We slowly start moving and finally get to the festival entrance at 4AM. Read that again. 12 hours later. 
We continued to sit in line  While the frantic security guards tried to show for us to our parking space which they did not have because they oversold the campground by thousands.  We were finally put on a grassy knoll next to the lake which was not even for our 33 foot long camper. We parked at 7:30A.  By the time that we got the RV set up, unpacked and got to rest it was close to 9A. We'd been up 27+ hours at this point and missed the pre party Wednesday night. 

 CONTINUE READING IN THE COMMENTS...GASOLINE

How cute are these over the knee rhinestone socks from @heaux_apparel !?

The top colors come in a variety including solid black,  white stripes and these rainbow stripes! Other colors are available too!

They are extra soft and don't slide down the knee. I didn't have to keep pulling them up after each pose.
